data.chText: 使（房间、建筑物等）通风；使通气
data.enText: to allow fresh air to enter and move around a room, building, etc.

data.chText: 这个浴室使用抽风扇通风。
data.enText: The bathroom is ventilated by means of an extractor fan.
to express your feelings or opinions publicly

data.chText: 在使用油漆前确保室内通风充足。
data.enText: Make sure that there is adequate ventilation in the room before using the paint.

simple_means.memory_skill: vent 风 + il 加强 + ate 使… → 通风

tr: expose to cool or cold air so as to cool or freshen
furnish with an opening to allow air to circulate or gas to escape
example: The architect did not think about ventilating the storage space
The graduates gave vent to cheers
The gust of air ventilated the room

tr: expose to the circulation of fresh air so as to retard spoilage

value.def: If you ventilate a room or building, you allow fresh air to get into it.

example.ex: Ventilate the room properly when paint stripping...
example.tran: 当油漆开始剥落时，要给房间适当通风。

example.ex: The pit is ventilated by a steel fan.
example.tran: 矿井中用钢制通风机来保持空气流通。

value.tran: 使（房间或建筑）通风;使空气流通

example.ex: The only ventilation comes from tiny sliding windows.
example.tran: 只能通过小推拉窗来通风。

value.def: If you ventilate your ideas or feelings, you talk about them or express them freely in front of other people.

example.ex: He did not think it the job of officials to ventilate their doubts or daydreams.
example.tran: 他认为公开提出自己的疑问或不切实际的想法并非官员们的分内之事。

partsOfSpeech.dec: vent 风 + il 加强 + ate 做，造成，使… → 通风
vent 风 + il 进入 + ator 器物 → 通风设备
